Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "smit" in different forms and positions:

1. Moram da *smitujem* ovaj softver. (I have to uninstall this software.)
2. Sinoć sam *smetala* komšijama svojom bukom. (Last night I disturbed my neighbors with my noise.)
3. *Smetnja* u mreži je uzrokovala prekid u radu. (A network disturbance caused a disruption in service.)
4. Kada nešto radim, *ne smeta mi* ništa drugo. (When I'm doing something, nothing else bothers me.)
5. Zašto *smetaš* svom bratu dok učiš? (Why are you disturbing your brother while he's studying?)
6. Kada sam videla koliko je prljavo, *smučilo* mi se da uđem u tu prostoriju. (When I saw how dirty it was, I felt disgusted to enter that room.)
7. U redu je ako *smitnemo* ovaj deo, ali onda moramo paziti na ostale delove. (It's okay if we remove this part, but then we have to be careful with the other parts.)
8. Molim vas, *ne smetajte* mi dok radim. (Please don't disturb me while I'm working.)
9. U ovom parku nema dovoljno kanti za smeće, ljudi *smeće* bacaju po travi. (There aren't enough trash cans in this park, people throw trash on the grass.)
10. Ne znam kako da *sredim* ovu situaciju, previše je komplikovana. (I don't know how to fix this situation, it's too complicated.)

I hope these examples are helpful!